195
00:08:59,907 --> 00:09:01,742 line:-2
Let me show you
how it looks like


196
00:09:01,775 --> 00:09:03,076 line:-1
in App Store Connect.


197
00:09:04,077 --> 00:09:07,814 line:-2
Here is the Builds Groups view,
where you will find builds


198
00:09:07,848 --> 00:09:12,085 line:-2
grouped by the Xcode Cloud
workflow and GIT branch.


199
00:09:13,086 --> 00:09:14,087 line:-1
They are supported


200
00:09:14,121 --> 00:09:17,157 line:-2
in the App Store Connect app
on iOS, too.


201
00:09:18,158 --> 00:09:20,527 line:-2
For internal testers
on TestFlight,


202
00:09:20.561 --> 00:09:23.564 line:-2 align:center
the Build Groups display
makes it easier


203
00:09:23.597 --> 00:09:27.434 line:-2 align:center
to find builds based on the more
familiar GIT branch names


204
00:09:27.467 --> 00:09:31.338 line:-2 align:center
and Xcode Cloud workflows
for internal testing.


205
00:09:32,339 --> 00:09:36,076 line:-2
You can also filter feedback
by a specific Build Group


206
00:09:36,109 --> 00:09:39,346 line:-2
under the Feedback section
in App Store Connect.


207
00:09:40.047 --> 00:09:42.382 line:-2 align:center
Well, these are
the amazing features


208
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:45,419 line:-2
of TestFlight
coming soon this year.


209
00:09:45.452 --> 00:09:48.455 line:-2 align:center
TestFlight on Mac supports
both native Mac apps


210
00:09:48,488 --> 00:09:51,325 line:-2
and iOS apps
on Apple Silicon Macs.


211
00:09:51,358 --> 00:09:55,395 line:-2
You can start beta testing
on Mac coming fall.


212
00:09:55.429 --> 00:09:57.464 line:-2 align:center
Improve
internal group management


213
00:09:57.497 --> 00:10:00.367 line:-2 align:center
to create multiple groups
as per your needs.


214
00:10:00,400 --> 00:10:01,468 line:-1
And finally,


215
00:10:01,502 --> 00:10:04,505 line:-2
Xcode Cloud integrates
with App Store Connect


216
00:10:04.538 --> 00:10:07.374 line:-2 align:center
and TestFlight to manage
build distribution


217
00:10:07.407 --> 00:10:09.843 line:-2 align:center
and organize them
by build groups.


